panels.description: Request duration = total time for the request received by client; http_req_sending + http_req_waiting + http_req_receiving

targets.query: SELECT mean("value") FROM "http_req_duration" WHERE ("type"::tag = 'fastapi') AND $timeFilter GROUP BY "requested_len"::tag

panels.title: GraphQL Request duration (ms) based on returned

panels.description: http_req_duration is Total time for the request. It’s equal to http_req_sending + http_req_waiting + http_req_receiving (i.e. how long did the remote server take to process the request and respond, without the initial DNS lookup/connection times). float; Grouped by 1 sec intervals

targets.query: SELECT max("value") FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT percentile("value", 95) FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE ("type"::tag = 'fastapi') AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT percentile("value", 90) FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE ("type"::tag = 'fastapi') AND $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT min("value") FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE ("type"::tag = 'fastapi') AND $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
